273
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,470
I was pretty sure I wanted you...

274
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:57,200
...but I just thought we should meet face to face.

275
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:59,090
I've made my decision.

276
00:11:59,830 --> 00:12:01,640
I choose them.

277
00:12:02,060 --> 00:12:04,380
Oh, my God, this is great.

278
00:12:04,430 --> 00:12:06,550
This is so great. Did you hear that?

279
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,210
Yeah, I did.

280
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:09,370
Hey.

281
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:13,130
Thank you. Thank you so much.

282
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:17,090
You are so going to heaven!

283
00:12:23,450 --> 00:12:25,870
We got some really great stuff.

284
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:27,080
Yeah.

285
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,770
Yeah, but I'm not sure about some of the bras I got.

286
00:12:30,190 --> 00:12:32,180
Really? Do you want to try some of them on for me?

287
00:12:32,180 --> 00:12:33,450
Okay.

288
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:36,640
Wait, are we in Joey's imagination?

289
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:42,640
Oh, no. I took one of Ross' bags by mistake.

290
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:44,270
And one of mine is missing.

291
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,700
Ross probably has it.

292
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:47,290
You'll get it from him later.

293
00:12:52,850 --> 00:12:55,630
So, what do you think?

294
00:12:58,220 --> 00:13:01,030
I think we're not wearing the same shirt anymore.

295
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:04,950
Yeah. Yeah, Rachel picked it out for me.

296
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:06,470
She told me to trust her, and you know what?

297
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:07,740
I'm glad I did.

298
00:13:07,790 --> 00:13:10,190
I turned quite a few heads on my way over here.

299
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:15,330
Dude, I really don't think you should be wearing that.

300
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:17,840
I see.

301
00:13:17,890 --> 00:13:21,390
Somebody's afraid of a little competition with the ladies?

302
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:25,000
Looks like someone is the ladies!

303
00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:29,270
You're just jealous because you couldn't pull this off.

304
00:13:29,530 --> 00:13:33,020
Yeah. Now if you'll excuse me, I have a date.

305
00:13:35,170 --> 00:13:38,570
See? All eyes on me!

306
00:13:44,510 --> 00:13:46,410
We are not signing those papers.

307
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:47,800
Why not?

308
00:13:47,850 --> 00:13:50,340
It's wrong. They made a mistake.

309
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:51,740
They think we're somebody else.

310
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:54,160
God works in mysterious ways.

311
00:13:54,950 --> 00:13:56,730
You have got to stop.

312
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:59,410
But she liked us.

313
00:13:59,460 --> 00:14:01,060
She likes Doctor Chandler

314
00:14:01,110 --> 00:14:02,420
and Reverend Monica.

315
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:04,300
If you think about it,

316
00:14:04,350 --> 00:14:06,080
I'm kind of like a reverend.

317
00:14:06,130 --> 00:14:09,840
I mean, as a chef, I serve God

318
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:12,790
by feeding the hungry and poor.

319
00:14:13,470 --> 00:14:16,360
Your veal chop is 34.95!

320
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:18,810
Come on,

321
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:20,930
I just-- I think we've been given an opportunity.

322
00:14:20,980 --> 00:14:22,520
The mistake's already made.

323
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:24,110
They're writing up the papers now.

324
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:26,070
But we're not the ones she chose.

325
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:28,480
How can you feel okay about this?

326
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:31,410
Because.

327
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:35,280
We may not be who she thinks we are...

328
00:14:35,330 --> 00:14:38,110
...but no one will ever love that baby more than us.

329
00:14:38,230 --> 00:14:40,210
- I know.  - I mean, who knows...

330
00:14:40,260 --> 00:14:41,700
...how long it's gonna take for someone else

331
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,250
to give us a baby?

332
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:45,950
What if no one ever picks us?

333
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,580
Oh, honey....

334
00:14:47,710 --> 00:14:49,260
Please?

335
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:51,930
Please. We are so close.

336
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:56,000
Monica, I want a baby too.

337
00:14:56,530 --> 00:14:58,920
But this woman is giving away her child.

338
00:14:58,970 --> 00:15:01,800
She deserves to know who it's going to.

339
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,990
Okay. You're right.

340
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:15,800
So we'll tell the truth.

341
00:15:15,850 --> 00:15:16,980
And who knows, you know?

342
00:15:17,030 --> 00:15:18,910
Maybe she'll like us for us.

343
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,360
Maybe she will.

344
00:15:24,410 --> 00:15:26,670
Why couldn't I have been a reverend?

345
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,170
You're Jewish.

346
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,950
Technicality!

347
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:39,870
Garden salad for the lady.

348
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:42,300
Oh, that looks great. Good ordering.

349
00:15:43,060 --> 00:15:45,710
Seafood platter for the gentleman,

350
00:15:45,710 --> 00:15:47,300
and extra fries.

351
00:15:47,350 --> 00:15:48,550
Enjoy.

352
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:52,950
Those fries look delicious.

353
00:15:53,150 --> 00:15:55,620
I didn't know you liked French fries.

354
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:58,090
Help yourself. What's mine is yours.

355
00:16:02,970 --> 00:16:05,000
Wow, are those stuffed clams?

356
00:16:09,450 --> 00:16:11,820
Yes, they are my stuffed clams.

357
00:16:14,230 --> 00:16:17,040
How about those fries, though, huh?

358
00:16:17,990 --> 00:16:20,720
- They are delicious.  - Yeah.

359
00:16:23,970 --> 00:16:27,010
You are beautiful, you know that?

360
00:16:28,540 --> 00:16:30,730
That is so sweet.

361
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:34,070
Okay, then.

362
00:16:45,860 --> 00:16:47,680
Now look what you did!

363
00:16:47,730 --> 00:16:50,400
What? What is the matter with you?

364
00:16:50,450 --> 00:16:51,630
I don't like it

365
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:54,490
when people take food off of my plate, okay?

366
00:16:54,540 --> 00:16:56,380
But you said, "What's mine is yours."

367
00:16:56,430 --> 00:16:58,000
Well, I didn't mean it!

368
00:16:59,460 --> 00:17:01,420
Fine. Sorry,

369
00:17:01,470 --> 00:17:03,750
I didn't think it was that big a deal.

370
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:07,260
No, I'm sorry. I....

371
00:17:07,310 --> 00:17:09,590
I'm overreacting, okay?

372
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:12,190
It's just, when it comes to food, l...

373
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,590
...have certain rules...

374
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,420
...okay? I mean...

375
00:17:15,470 --> 00:17:17,430
...there are things you do,

376
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:20,390
and, you know, things that you don't do.

377
00:17:27,630 --> 00:17:29,580
Wow, this place looks great.

378
00:17:29,630 --> 00:17:30,990
Oh, you are gonna love it.

379
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:34,240
And I'm so glad we're finally doing this.

380
00:17:34,290 --> 00:17:36,730
- Me too.  - Here.

381
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:47,350
So this was fun.

382
00:17:56,060 --> 00:17:58,900
I really am sorry about, you know, before.

383
00:17:58,950 --> 00:18:00,700
And I want to make sure you know

384
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:02,150
I really do like you.

385
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:05,120
Sure, just not as much as clams.

386
00:18:05,170 --> 00:18:06,820
Well, stuffed clams....

387
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:10,890
Chocolate torte for the lady.

388
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:12,970
Cheesecake for the gentleman.

389
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:14,480
Excuse me, sir.

390
00:18:14,530 --> 00:18:17,550
There seems to be some sort of red crap on my cheesecake.

391
00:18:19,210 --> 00:18:21,520
Yes, that's a raspberry coulis.

392
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:23,220
I'm so stupid ordering cheesecake,

393
00:18:23,220 --> 00:18:24,840
trying to be healthy.

394
00:18:37,980 --> 00:18:39,890
Oh, no.

395
00:18:40,270 --> 00:18:42,030
This is work. I should call in.

396
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:43,370
Can you excuse me?

397
00:18:43,420 --> 00:18:45,330
Yeah, sure. No problem.

398
00:18:47,780 --> 00:18:49,020
What are you doing?

399
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:51,250
I thought you don't share food?

400
00:18:51,300 --> 00:18:52,730
Sure I do.

401
00:18:52,780 --> 00:18:54,060
Coulis?

402
00:18:54,990 --> 00:18:57,990
No. If I can't have your clams,

403
00:18:58,040 --> 00:18:59,270
you can't have my dessert.

404
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:00,620
This is a two-way street.

405
00:19:03,330 --> 00:19:04,580
Really?

406
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:07,110
Really.

407
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:10,090
Now this all better be here when I come back.

408
00:19:10,140 --> 00:19:13,560
Yeah, of course. I can control myself.

409
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:28,170
Stop staring at me!

410
00:19:39,370 --> 00:19:41,990
Just a tiny little....

411
00:19:56,390 --> 00:19:58,780
I'm not even sorry.

412
00:20:02,930 --> 00:20:04,660
- Hi.  - Hey.

413
00:20:05,250 --> 00:20:09,130
So these are the preliminary forms for an open adoption.

414
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:10,550
There's a lot to go over,

415
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,470
but I'll explain as we go through.

416
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:16,720
- Is that a picture? - Yeah.

417
00:20:16,770 --> 00:20:19,360
It's a sonogram they took of the baby last week.

418
00:20:19,410 --> 00:20:21,230
I thought you might want to see it.

419
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:30,220
Look, doctor.

420
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:36,160
Look, before we sign anything,

421
00:20:36,210 --> 00:20:38,040
we really have to talk.

422
00:20:41,350 --> 00:20:43,460
We're not who you think we are.

423
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:44,870
I don't understand.

424
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:46,710
The agency must have made a mistake.

425
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:47,970
My wife is not a reverend,

426
00:20:48,020 --> 00:20:49,610
and I'm not a doctor.

427
00:20:49,730 --> 00:20:51,710
- What? - That's impossible.

428
00:20:51,830 --> 00:20:53,430
I could perform an operation on you

429
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,960
and prove it if you'd like.

430
00:20:56,930 --> 00:20:59,650
I have to check your file. Excuse me.

431
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:01,600
So who are you?

432
00:21:01,770 --> 00:21:05,190
Our names really are Monica and Chandler. We're from New York.

433
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:07,460
Yeah, but the important thing to know about us...

434
00:21:07,510 --> 00:21:11,030
...is how much we would care for this little baby.

435
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:13,240
So you lied to me before?

436
00:21:13,290 --> 00:21:16,790
Well, we "bore false witness."

437
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:20,170
See? I could be a reverend.

438
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:23,270
I can't believe this.

439
00:21:23,540 --> 00:21:25,880
But we were hoping that since we told you the truth...

440
00:21:25,930 --> 00:21:27,530
...that you still might consider--

441
00:21:27,580 --> 00:21:29,380
Giving you my baby?

442
00:21:29,430 --> 00:21:31,840
You think I'd give you my child after this?

443
00:21:31,890 --> 00:21:32,970
You don't have to decide now.

444
00:21:33,020 --> 00:21:34,540
If you look at our file--

445
00:21:34,590 --> 00:21:37,190
I don't want to look at your file. This is over.

446
00:21:42,010 --> 00:21:43,510
Erica, wait.

447
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:45,880
I have nothing to say to you.

448
00:21:45,930 --> 00:21:48,260
Look, you have every reason to be upset.

449
00:21:48,310 --> 00:21:49,900
We did lie.

450
00:21:49,950 --> 00:21:51,640
But only because we've been waiting

451
00:21:51,690 --> 00:21:54,340
and trying to have a baby for so long.

452
00:21:54,390 --> 00:21:56,090
And we don't know how long it's gonna be

453
00:21:56,140 --> 00:21:57,770
before we get another chance again.

454
00:21:57,890 --> 00:22:00,070
Why don't you ask the reverend to pray on it?

455
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:03,050
Erica, please.

456
00:22:03,100 --> 00:22:05,190
Just consider us.

457
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:07,160
Ask them to see our file.

458
00:22:07,950 --> 00:22:09,620
Our last name's Bing.

459
00:22:09,740 --> 00:22:12,380
My wife's a chef, and I'm in advertising.

460
00:22:13,620 --> 00:22:14,970
Oh, yeah.

461
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:17,600
I actually liked you guys.

462
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:20,440
But it doesn't matter.

463
00:22:20,490 --> 00:22:21,730
Because what you did was wrong.

464
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:23,890
But you did like us.

465
00:22:24,630 --> 00:22:26,270
And you should.

466
00:22:27,020 --> 00:22:29,250
My wife's an incredible woman.

467
00:22:29,690 --> 00:22:33,290
She is loving, and devoted and caring.

468
00:22:33,900 --> 00:22:35,680
And don't tell her I said this,

469
00:22:35,730 --> 00:22:37,370
but the woman's always right.

470
00:22:41,730 --> 00:22:44,700
I love my wife more than anything in this world.

471
00:22:46,310 --> 00:22:47,760
And it...

472
00:22:49,260 --> 00:22:52,160
It kills me that I can't give her a baby.

473
00:22:58,060 --> 00:22:59,930
I really want a kid.

474
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:02,750
And when that day finally comes,

475
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,810
I'll learn how to be a good dad.

476
00:23:05,770 --> 00:23:07,110
But my wife...

477
00:23:07,860 --> 00:23:09,810
...she's already there.

478
00:23:10,550 --> 00:23:12,060
She's a mother...

479
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:15,220
...without a baby.

480
00:23:22,820 --> 00:23:24,350
Please?

481
00:23:36,450 --> 00:23:38,180
You still want that baby?

482
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:56,570
God bless you, Chandler Bing!

483
00:24:10,010 --> 00:24:13,260
Turns out this sweater is made for a woman.

484
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:17,090
So why are you still wearing it?

485
00:24:17,090 --> 00:24:18,720
Because it's soft.

486
00:24:20,540 --> 00:24:22,570
Hey, so how was your date?

487
00:24:22,570 --> 00:24:23,840
Not so good.

488
00:24:26,420 --> 00:24:29,500
Well, looks like it's just the two of us tonight,

489
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:30,560
huh, buddy?

490
00:24:31,070 --> 00:24:32,630
Yeah. And you know what?

491
00:24:32,630 --> 00:24:34,040
We could do a lot worse.

492
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:35,670
- Yeah. - Yeah.

493
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:41,880
Joey doesn't share food!

